com.edinarobotics.utils.log

Class LogEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.edinarobotics.utils.log.LogEvent

  • public final class LogEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an event being logged by the logging system. This class tracks all aspects of a loggable event such as its severity level, the message, the original logger to which it was submitted, and an optional Throwable associated with the event.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns a String representation of this LogEvent. The String representation can span either one or two lines depending on whether or not this LogEvent has an associated Throwable. The String has the form: [-level name-] -original logger name-: -message- -Throwable- If no Throwable is associated with this LogEvent, the second line is omitted.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
